WEBVTT

00:02.235 --> 00:03.759
lts trajectory is erratic.

00:03.836 --> 00:06.635
And our sensors aren't detecting
any stellar or planetary

00:06.705 --> 00:08.970
gravitational fields that could
account for its motion.

00:09.042 --> 00:11.203
Then you're saying
it isn't a comet.

00:11.277 --> 00:15.407
And yet, it looks, feels and
tastes just like a comet.

00:15.482 --> 00:17.143
Well, there's a slight chance

00:17.217 --> 00:20.118
there are magnetodynamic forces
acting on the comet

00:20.186 --> 00:22.746
that are too subtle
for our sensors to detect.

00:23.790 --> 00:26.987
Or it might be something
we've never encountered before.

00:27.093 --> 00:28.890
B'Elanna, go down
to Transporter Room 2.

00:28.962 --> 00:31.192
Let's beam aboard a sample
for examination.

00:31.264 --> 00:32.662
Aye, Captain.

00:32.732 --> 00:35.200
Harry, see if you
can lock onto a core fragment.

00:36.369 --> 00:38.963
Having no trouble penetrating
the crust, Captain.

00:39.039 --> 00:41.303
Janeway to Torres.

00:41.374 --> 00:43.274
We're ready when you are,
Lieutenant.

00:43.343 --> 00:45.777
Setting up a class-3
containment field, Captain.

00:45.845 --> 00:47.244
Field in place.

00:47.313 --> 00:48.837
Commence transport.

00:48.915 --> 00:50.075
Energizing.

00:52.000 --> 00:58.074
